bilingual.source: By coincidence, we met at the same restaurant.
bilingual.target: 我们在同一家餐厅碰面，真是一个巧合。

bilingual.source: What a coincidence that we have the same favorite book!
bilingual.target: 我们喜欢同一本书，真是一个巧合。

bilingual.source: The coincidence of their birthdays is quite remarkable.
bilingual.target: 他们的生日是同一天，真是一个了不起的巧合。

bilingual.source: The simultaneity of the discoveries was a remarkable coincidence.
bilingual.target: 这些发现的同时性是一个了不起的巧合。

bilingual.source: It was pure coincidence that they both chose the same vacation spot.
bilingual.target: 他们俩选择了同一个度假地点，纯属巧合。

bilingual.source: It was a strange coincidence that we both wore the same outfit today.
bilingual.target: 我们今天穿了同样的衣服，真是一个奇怪的巧合。

bilingual.source: I still can't believe what a coincidence it was.
bilingual.target: 我仍然不能相信这是多么巧合。

bilingual.source: This is not coincidence, nor is it our business to stand in judgement to Fred.
bilingual.target: 这不是巧合，我们也没有义务去评判Fred。

yingyinNormal.en: It was just a coincidence. I was taking some overdue holiday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 巧合而已，我在那休假。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon, it's an amazing coincidence. Can we leave it at that?
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿，这是一个奇妙的巧合，就这样了行吗？

yingyinNormal.en: That's a hell of a coincidence. All right, we're going to pay CCTV a little visit. Let's roll.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是巧合啊，我们得去趟监控中心，走吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Your memory? The date carved beneath. Six, 10 and 21. Coincidence?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你记忆中的木马？底部刻的日期。2021年6月10日。这是巧合么？

yingyinNormal.en: All the wealthy and beautiful people in movies ride Jet Skis. That can't just be a coincidence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 电影里有钱又帅的人都骑摩托艇，这不可能是巧合。

yingyinNormal.en: A dangerous coincidence. I always knew you were special. Maybe this is how.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个巧合很危险。我一直都觉得 你很特别。也许这就是你的特别之处。

yingyinNormal.en: It's not a coincidence. Someone has been playing intricate games and has made pawns of us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这肯定不是巧合，肯定有人在背后操纵 ，还利用了我们。

yingyinNormal.en: And it was no coincidence that around that time I started getting good at the violin, the guitar and the drums.
yingyinNormal.zh: 并不是巧合，我那时开始玩小提琴，吉他，鼓，玩得越来越好。

yingyinNormal.en: You wanna hear a freakish coincidence? Guess who's doing laundry there too? Who? Me. Was that not clear?
yingyinNormal.zh: 想知道有个巧合吗？猜猜谁也要去洗衣店？谁？我。难道还不够清楚？

yingyinNormal.en: You sure it's Ortiz? My gun at the crime scene? It's not a coincidence. He offered to clean it for me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你确定是奥蒂兹？我的枪在犯罪现场，这不是巧合，他之前主动要帮我清理。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, well, this would be one of those circumstances that people unfamiliar with the law of large numbers would call a coincidence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是那些不熟悉数学规律的人会称之为巧合的事件之一了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I wouldn't count on it tonight. Doesn't it strike you as, just a little bit of coincidence, the timing of everything?
yingyinNormal.zh: 今晚就别指望了，我这样说会不会打击你？所有事情都这么巧合？

yingyinNormal.en: Ooh, what a coincidence. Maybe you can discuss with him while you're playing in the tournament. Sign here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天呐，多么神奇的巧合啊。你也许可以跟他在锦标赛中讨论一下，在这签字。

yingyinNormal.en: It's no coincidence. He bought that house to be near her. He threw all those parties hoping she'd wander in one night.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这绝非巧合，他买下那房子，就是为了接近她，他办那些派对，就是希望她能来一次。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, that's just coincidence. Yeah, I'm sure. Make her available this afternoon for a supervised deposition or be held in contempt.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这只是巧合。我想也是，让她今天下午准备参加受监督的取证，否则就是蔑视法庭。

yingyinNormal.en: The flags of Liechtenstein and Haiti were identical by coincidence, a fact that wasn't discovered until they competed against each other at the 1936 Olympics.
yingyinNormal.zh: 列支敦斯登和海地的国旗以前碰巧是一样的，直到两国在1936年奥运会对战时才发现这个巧合。

yingyinNormal.en: You use it to get your way. I use it to get the right way. The fact that the right way is also my way is a happy coincidence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你就拿它来给自己行方便了呀。我是拿它来做该做的事，事实证明，该做的事就是给我自己行方便，这真是个美妙的巧合。

yingyinNormal.en: It's not just a coincidence. The only reason you delivered our kids was because our doctor's appendix burst, and now Kate's appendix brought us all back here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这绝不是巧合。当年正因为我们的医生阑尾破裂才换你给我们的孩子接生，现在凯特的阑尾炎把我们全家带回这里。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, what a coincidence. It's the future Mrs. Wolowitz.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是太巧了，她才是未来的沃罗威茨夫人。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a strange coincidence. What is? The fact that Gatsby's house is just across the bay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是太巧了。什么太巧了？盖茨比的房子和他们家就一水之隔。
